- Password hashing
- Session-based authentication
- Login protection using @login_required
- CSRF protection with Flask-WTF
- Secure file upload handling for payment proofs

### Testing Strategy
- Manual testing of authentication flows
- Validation of payout order generation
- Payment tracking verification
- User acceptance testing with savings group participants

### Database Design:
#### ER Diagram
```mermaid

erDiagram

    USER {
        int id PK
        string full_name
        string email
        string password_hash
        datetime created_at
    }

    GROUP {
        int id PK
        string name
        float contribution_amount
        int payout_frequency_days
        datetime created_at
    }

    GROUPMEMBER {
        int id PK
        int user_id FK
        int group_id FK
        int payout_position
        boolean has_received
    }

    PAYOUTSCHEDULE {
        int id PK
        date payout_date
        int recipient_id FK
        int group_id FK
    }

    PAYMENT {
        int id PK
        int payer_id FK
        int payout_id FK
        float amount
        string proof_image
        datetime paid_at
    }

    USER ||--o{ GROUPMEMBER : joins
    GROUP ||--o{ GROUPMEMBER : has_members

    GROUP ||--o{ PAYOUTSCHEDULE : schedules

    USER ||--o{ PAYMENT : makes
    PAYOUTSCHEDULE ||--o{ PAYMENT : collects

    USER ||--o{ PAYOUTSCHEDULE : receives

```
